Speed ain't a useless stat, but I think that brute's mistake was to invest too much on it. A certain amount is enough to make all the difference in a battle. I have a brute like his who got lightning bolt at level 2, and then reconnaissance at level 3, so her speed stat shot up to 37 and she hardly looks any slower than other brutes with higher speeds. After level 3, I stacked up on some good skills in order to compensate for the fact that my initiative was reduced by 200 rather than investing too much on my speed stat which was already high. I've only ever picked to increase her speed stat once since she got lightning bolt and reconnaissance

6th sense
Fist of fury
Hostility
Shield
Reconnaissance
Lightning bolt

In my opinion, I've handled my speed brute properly
